Samuel Naeranus, acccording to Charles Peyran’s Histoire de l’Academie de Scdan, was born at Dort about 1580, succeeded Berehet in chair of Rhetoric at Sedan in 1605, and died at Amersfort in 1642. He was the composer of verses prefixed to the Code of Regulations for Discipline of the Students at Sedan in 1608, of which excellent regula- tions Mons. Brincourt has furnished a reprint. If Naeranus died as late as 1642,

the title of Johnston’s poem is more probably “on Samuel Naeranus’s funereal tears‚” referring to his Elegiae poems on others.
